  <static seed="95" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Laney and Brent are sharing a pizza. Laney ate <m>{{\frac{1}{8}}}</m> of the pizza, and Brent ate <m>{{\frac{1}{10}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Laney eat than Brent?</p>
<p>Laney ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Brent ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{40}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{8}}} - {{\frac{1}{10}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 5}{8 \cdot 5}-\frac{1 \cdot 4}{10 \cdot 4} \\
      \amp = \frac{5}{40} - \frac{4}{40} \\
      \amp = \frac{5-4}{40} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{40}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Laney ate <m>{{\frac{1}{40}}}</m> more of the pizza than Brent ate.</p>
</solution>
